  "prompt": "How much does it cost to learn at Oxford aviation academy?",
  "response": "The cost of training at Oxford Aviation Academy (now known as CAE Oxford Aviation Academy) can vary significantly based on the type of course or program you are enrolling in. As of the latest information, a full-time integrated ATPL (Airline Transport Pilot License) program, which is a comprehensive course designed to take students from little or no flying experience to fully qualified airline pilots, can cost around \u00a370,000 to \u00a3130,000.\n\nKeep in mind that this is a rough estimate and actual prices may vary. Additionally, there may be other costs associated such as accommodation, transport, equipment, and living expenses. It is advisable to contact CAE Oxford Aviation Academy directly or visit their official website for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding fees and other related costs.",
